OL,6,F"In the context of where and how this
OL,7,Foffence was committed, and in
OL,8,Fparticular, bearing in mind the
OL,9,Fpropensity of violence in schools
OL,10,Fperpetrated by pupils, it seems to me
OL,11,Fthat my public duty require that only
OL,12,Fa prison sentence can be passed here,"
OL,13,Fthe judge told Felton's defence team.
OL,15,FFelton, of Gorseinon, was remanded
OL,16,Finto custody until he is sentenced on
OL,17,FApril 25.
